{"DIAGEOTROPIC":[{"def":"Relating to, or exhibiting, diageotropism.","pos":""}],"DIAGEOTROPISM":[{"def":"The tendency of organs (as roots) of plants to assume a position oblique or transverse to a direction towards the center of the earth.","pos":""}],"DIAGLYPH":[{"def":"Represented or formed by depressions in the general surface; as, diaglyphic sculpture or engraving; -- opposed to anaglyphic.","pos":""}],"DIAGNOSE":[{"def":"To ascertain by diagnosis; to diagnosticate.","pos":""}],"DIAGNOSIS":[{"def":"The art or act of recognizing the presence of disease from its signs or symptoms, and deciding as to its character; also, the decision arrived at.","pos":""}],"DIAGNOSTIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or furnishing, a diagnosis; indicating the nature of a disease.","pos":""}],"DIAGNOSTICATE":[{"def":"To make a diagnosis of; to recognize by its symptoms, as a disease.","pos":""}],"DIAGNOSTICS":[{"def":"That part of medicine which has to do with ascertaining the nature of diseases by means of their symptoms or signs.","pos":""}],"DIAGOMETER":[{"def":"A sort of electroscope, invented by Rousseau, in which the dry pile is employed to measure the amount of electricity transmitted by different bodies, or to determine their conducting power.","pos":""}],"DIAGONAL":[{"def":"Joining two not adjacent angles of a quadrilateral or multilateral figure; running across from corner to corner; crossing at an angle with one of the sides.","pos":""}],"DIAGONALLY":[{"def":"In a diagonal direction.","pos":""}],"DIAGONIAL":[{"def":"Diagonal; diametrical; hence; diametrically opposed.","pos":""}],"DIAGRAM":[{"def":"A figure or drawing made to illustrate a statement, or facilitate a demonstration; a plan.","pos":""}],"DIAGRAMMATIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or of the nature of, a diagram; showing by diagram.","pos":""}],"DIAGRAPH":[{"def":"A drawing instrument, combining a protractor and scale.","pos":""}],"DIAGRAPHICS":[{"def":"The art or science of descriptive drawing; especially, the art or science of drawing by mechanical appliances and mathematical rule.","pos":""}]}